p2
VGems of the past
p3
sVnews
p4
VVignana Samithi of Hyderabad organised a three-day festival celebrating Ramadasu&#8217;s 388th Jayanthi, Purandaradasa&#8217;s 538th Jayanthi and Annamacharya&#8217;s 600th Jayanthi. The participating vocalists presented popular compositions of all the three saint musicians and also fresh numbers particularly of Annamacharya. The function was held at Anandnagar community hall. The music sessions had group rendition of compositions led by Suri Venkateswaralu, with children and women too participating in good number. The other solo artistes sang other compositions not repeating what the group rendered. The sabha also released brochures showcasing the life of all the three Vaggeyakaras.The festival opened with the rendition of Ramadasu&#8217;s compositions in the company of Challa Maruthi Kiran on keyboard and Sriramakrishna on mridangam. This was followed by a concert by Y.Ramaprabha, a well known artiste of the city. She is not only one of the leading vocalists but is also known for promoting Carnatic music, through a separate organisation. She began with aslokamand then renderedBhajare Sriramam,Diname Sudinamu Kodanda RamaandNanu Brovamani Cheppave. The last number in Kalyani was treated as a concert piece, with the vocalist presentingragaessay,nerevalandswaraprasthara.Naraharini Nammaka Narula Nammitiwas a moving composition.This was followed by another concert of Dr.Vizarsu Balasubramanyam, who rendered some select compositions likeMaruthi Namosthute,Ramabhadra RaraandHarihara Rama,Vunnaado Ledo KamalanayanaandVasudeva Entapani chesitivi. O.Rajasekhar on violin and Burra Sriram on mridangam lent support to the vocalists.On the second day, Purandaradasu&#8217;s Jayanthi was celebrated. All the participants presentedSarali swaralu, Janta swaralu, AlankaraluandPillari geethaluthat constitute the fundamentals of Carnatic music.This was followed by a concert by Vasantha Lakshmi, who rendered Purandaradasa&#8217;s compositions that includedTava Saranam Jasanakanain Bilahari,JagadodharanaMisra Kapi,Tambura Matiravain Sindhu Bhairavi,Dayamado Rangain Kalyani. The third day events were marked by S.Venumadhav&#8217;s recital of Annamacharyakirtanas.He sangfresh numbers composed by him and avoiding the popular ones.Adi Choodare Mohana Roopam, Ithade Parabrahma, Maruni Nagari DandamaandMoode Maatalu Moode Mulluwere well received. G.B.Sankar Rao, who is doing research into the works of Tallapaka Kavulu, gave an absorbing commentary on each compositiongiving out its gist. N.C.Ananthakrishna on violin and A.Sankara Rao on mridangam lent support to the artistes.
